$ kil.ps1

`kil.ps1` is a → Windows/PowerShell script to kill → Windows/development/process[processes] by their name. It might be called like so:
code {
PS C:\> kil excel
code }

The script can be given the `-restart` (or `-r`) argument to restart the process. If multiple processes were killed, only one process is restarted:
code {
PS C:\> kil -r outlook
code }

